Q7. Why is PCL a better choice than PLGA in making scaffolds for skull regeneration?a. Glass transition temperature (−60 °C vs 40–60 °C)b. Melting temperature (60 °C vs 240 °C)c. Degradation time (2–3 years vs &lt;6 months)d. Mechanical properties (&gt;200 MPa vs 20–30 MPa)


