Ceramic and Metal Biomaterials: Types, Manufacturing, and Applications | 陶瓷與金屬生物材料：類型、製造與應用Ceramic | 陶瓷Ceramic Types &amp; Manufacturing | 陶瓷類型與製造
Traditional Ceramics: Porcelain, Stoneware, Earthenware; each uses unique chemical compositions and raw materials. The Hong Kong&#x2F;Canton region is known for specialized techniques.傳統陶瓷： 瓷器、炻器、陶器；各自採用獨特的化學成分和原材料。港粵地區以專門工藝著稱。
Manufacturing Process: Clay (powder + water) is shaped, dried (shrinks and reorganizes), then fired&#x2F;sintered to bond particles.製造過程： 粘土（粉末+水）成型、乾燥（收縮與重組）、燒結使顆粒結合。
Materials: Kaolinite and Bentonite clays; Flint and Quartz additives reduce shrinkage; Feldspar creates glossy, non-porous finishes.原材料： 高嶺土和膨潤土；燧石和石英添加劑減少收縮；長石形成光滑致密表面。

Biomedical Ceramic Classifications | 生物醫學陶瓷分類
Bioactive Ceramics: Bond with tissue (e.g., glass ceramics for implant coatings, stimulate hydroxyapatite formation).生物活性陶瓷： 能與組織結合（如用於植入物塗層的玻璃陶瓷，促進羥基磷灰石形成）。
Bioresorbable Ceramics: Biodegradable (e.g., calcium phosphate compounds, hydroxyapatite).生物可吸收陶瓷： 可降解（如磷酸鈣化合物、羥基磷灰石）。
Bioinert Ceramics: Minimal tissue interaction (e.g., pyrolytic carbon, alumina for joint replacements and dental crowns).生物惰性陶瓷： 與組織相互作用極少（如用於關節置換和牙冠的熱解碳、氧化鋁）。

Natural Ceramics in the Body | 體內天然陶瓷
Bone: ~60% minerals (mainly hydroxyapatite), ~26% collagen, plus cells. Cortical (dense) and trabecular (porous) types; bone marrow contains stem and immune cells.骨骼： 約60%礦物質（主要為羥基磷灰石）、約26%膠原蛋白及細胞。分為緻密骨和鬆質骨；骨髓含有幹細胞和免疫細胞。
Teeth: Higher inorganic content; layers include enamel, dentin, and pulp. Strength from nanostructured calcium phosphate.牙齒： 無機物含量更高；分為琺瑯質、牙本質和牙髓。強度來自奈米結構磷酸鈣。

Sintering Process &amp; Applications | 燒結工藝與應用
Sintering: Occurs at ~⅓ melting point; surface atoms bond without full melting.燒結： 在約熔點三分之一溫度下進行，表面原子結合但未完全熔化。
Applications: Thermal spray coatings, porous structures for cell migration, dental crowns (zirconia vs. alumina), hip implants with hydroxyapatite coatings.應用： 熱噴塗塗層、細胞遷移的多孔結構、牙冠（氧化鋯與氧化鋁）、帶羥基磷灰石塗層的髖關節植入物。

Overview of Biomedical Materials | 生物醫學材料概述
Ceramics: Biocompatible, mainly for implant coatings.陶瓷： 生物相容性好，主要用於植入物塗層。
Metals: High mechanical strength, used for load-bearing implants.金屬： 機械強度高，用於承重植入物。

Ceramic Manufacturing &amp; Applications | 陶瓷製造與應用
Steps: Raw material prep, shaping, drying, sintering.步驟： 原料準備、成型、乾燥、燒結。
Applications: Dental&#x2F;orthopedic coatings, surface treatments to minimize protein&#x2F;cell deposition and reduce friction.應用： 牙科&#x2F;骨科塗層，表面處理減少蛋白質&#x2F;細胞沉積和摩擦。

Metals | 金屬Types &amp; Properties of Medical Metals | 醫用金屬類型與性質
Stainless Steel: Affordable, but poor corrosion resistance.不銹鋼： 價格低廉，但耐腐蝕性差。
Cobalt-Based Alloys: Better corrosion resistance, but potential carcinogenic ion release.鈷基合金： 耐腐蝕性更好，但可能釋放致癌離子。
Titanium Alloys: Best biocompatibility and corrosion resistance, non-toxic, but expensive.鈦合金： 生物相容性和耐腐蝕性最佳，無毒但價格昂貴。

Special Metal Materials | 特殊金屬材料
Shape Memory Alloys: Nickel-Titanium; used in braces, stents, IVC filters; return to shape when heated.形狀記憶合金： 鎳鈦合金；用於牙套、支架、下腔靜脈濾器，加熱後可恢復原形。
Liquid Metals: Solid at room temp, liquid at body temp; used in wearable electronics (e.g., mercury, gallium).液態金屬： 常溫為固體，體溫為液體；用於可穿戴電子（如汞、鎵）。
Biodegradable Metals: Magnesium- and zinc-based; gradually absorbed by the body.可降解金屬： 鎂基和鋅基金屬，能被人體逐漸吸收。

Corrosion Issues &amp; Protection | 腐蝕問題與防護
Mechanism: Oxidation, electrode formation, accelerated by moisture&#x2F;oxygen.機制： 氧化、電極形成，受潮濕&#x2F;氧氣加速。
Biological Impact: Corrosion products trigger immune response and inflammation, may cause bone degradation.生物影響： 腐蝕產物引發免疫反應和炎症，可能導致骨質破壞。
Protection: Use corrosion-resistant metals (chromium, titanium), inert ceramic coatings, and protective oxide layers.防護措施： 採用耐腐蝕金屬（鉻、鈦）、惰性陶瓷塗層和保護性氧化層。


